div.p:
My Lord, you haue had still the practise of Religion in your house, and one of the best helpes to further you, your worthy and religious Lady, whose name smelleth now like the wine of Lebanon, when shee is gone,Hosea 14.7. and now she enjoyeth the fruit of that, when neither her Nobilitie, birth, or worldly honour profited nothing; and this I write unto your LP: beseeching you to goe on in that Christian course, that both by your place and example, you may draw others unto the truth. The Lord promised that he would giue the uttermost parts of the earth for a possession to his Sonne;
      Psal. 2.8. this is the Motto of this Iland, and the farther

 North, it is the nearer to the ends of the earth, studie therefore my good Lord, that Iesus Christ may haue his possession enlarged in the North, and this shall be your crowne in the latter day, when all your possessions shall faile you.
